text:
Ross Watson (born in &lt;a href="Brisbane"&gt;Brisbane&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Australia"&gt;Australia&lt;/a&gt; in 1962) is an artist. He has exhibited in many solo and group exhibitions since 1984, including important surveys of Australian and international contemporary art at the &lt;a href="National%20Gallery%20of%20Australia"&gt;National Gallery of Australia&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href="National%20Gallery%20of%20Victoria"&gt;National Gallery of Victoria&lt;/a&gt;, and in the &lt;a href="Toronto"&gt;Toronto&lt;/a&gt; and Melbourne International Art Fairs. He has been described as a 'proud, gay man', and sexuality has inspired several of his works.
Ross's work includes portraits of Australian former &lt;a href="rugby%20league"&gt;rugby league&lt;/a&gt; footballer &lt;a href="Ian%20Roberts%20%28rugby%20league%29"&gt;Ian Roberts&lt;/a&gt;, and Olympic Champion &lt;a href="Matthew%20Mitcham"&gt;Matthew Mitcham&lt;/a&gt;
In 2012, Ross celebrated 25 years as a professional artist. His art is included in the collections of the &lt;a href="National%20Gallery%20of%20Australia"&gt;National Gallery of Australia&lt;/a&gt;, National Gallery of Victoria, &lt;a href="National%20Portrait%20Gallery%20%28Australia%29"&gt;National Portrait Gallery&lt;/a&gt;, and significant private collections including &lt;a href="Sir%20Elton%20John"&gt;Sir Elton John&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="James%20J.%20O%27Donnell"&gt;James J. O'Donnell&lt;/a&gt; and James D, Wolfensohn. He also did free work in aid of the &lt;a href="AIDS"&gt;AIDS&lt;/a&gt; charity, the &lt;a href="Terence%20Higgins%20Trust"&gt;Terence Higgins Trust&lt;/a&gt;
The internationally released book which includes an interview with the artist by former High Court Justice, the &lt;a href="Michael%20Kirby%20%28judge%29"&gt;Hon. Michael Kirby&lt;/a&gt;, is published by &lt;a href="Bruno%20Gm%C3%BCnder%20Verlag"&gt;Bruno Gmünder Verlag&lt;/a&gt; Germany.
